    "content": "<p>Anti-Markownikoff's addition of $$\\mathrm{HBr}$$ is observed in</p>",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "propene\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "but-2-ene\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "pent-2-ene\n"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "All of these"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>According to anti-Markownikoffs rule, in the presence of peroxide, addition of $$\\mathrm{HBr}$$ takes place to unsymmeterical double bond in such a way that $$\\mathrm{Br}^{-}$$ ions adds with carbon having more number of H-atoms.</p>\n<p>$$\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{CH}=\\mathrm{CH}_2+\\mathrm{HBr} \\xrightarrow{R \\mathrm{OOR}} \\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{CH}_2-\\mathrm{CH}_2 \\mathrm{Br}$$</p>",
    "topic": null,
    "year": 2023,
    "yearKey": "bitsat-2023",
    "difficulty": null
  },
